factions}{\*\cs11\fs20  to interact and trade with. The characters form a }{\*\cs16\fs20\b\i company}{\*\cs11\fs20 , the purpose of which is to make enough money to escape their miserable existences.\par To play }
{\*\cs13\fs20\b0\i Lavender Hack}{\*\cs11\fs20 , you will need 4, 6, 8, 10, 12, and 20 sided dice. The shorthand d20 refers to the twenty-sided die. The shorthand 3d6 refers to rolling three six-sided dice and adding the results together. The shorthand d100 refers to rolling two ten sided dice and using one die for the tens digit to generate a number from 1 to 100.\par Each player will need a copy of a }
{\*\cs16\fs20\b\i character sheet}{\*\cs11\fs20 , and the group will need a copy of the }{\*\cs16\fs20\b\i company sheet}{\*\cs11\fs20
. There are also }{\*\cs16\fs20\b\i exploration sheets}{\*\cs11\fs20  which can be useful during exploration. All of these sheets are located at the back of the book, as well as at ziapeltagames.com.\par }
