{\*\cs11\fs20 Usage dice might be rolled for a variety of reasons. If the result of rolling a usage die is a }{\*\cs14\fs20\b\i0
1-3}{\*\cs11\fs20 , the die is }{\*\cs16\fs20\b\i stepped down}{\*\cs11\fs20  in addition to any other potential effects. The more usage dice are rolled, the more they\rquote re used up! A 1, 2, or 3 result means the thing was }
{\*\cs16\fs20\b\i used}{\*\cs11\fs20 , and can occasionally trigger an additional effect besides stepping the die type down.\par This process of rolling a usage die, checking the result, and then determining if it should be stepped down is called a }
{\*\cs16\fs20\b\i usage test}{\*\cs11\fs20 . Frequently the only thing that matters in a usage test is if the die is stepped down or not.\par }
\pard\plain \s6\f0\fs24\ltrpar\ql\fi0\li0\ri0\sb180\sa0\facenter\sl288\slmult1\expnd0\expndtw0\cf0\up0\charscalex100\keepn\b0\i\ul0\strike0\accnone\hyphpar1\lang1033
